descript.supplinf:
Please acknowledge SanGIS as a source when SanGIS data are used in the preparation of reports, papers, publications, maps, and other products.
SanGIS notes that the original source is COGO which is a computer program that is used to calculate coordinate geometry. It is used to solve the geometric problems encountered in civil engineering applications including: property boundary and right of way surveys highway and interchange design construction layout bridge geometry
